commit_message:
storage: bases of a Cassandra driver

This is a basic implementation of a Cassandra driver. For now, it only
supports storing samples collected into a Cassandra column family.

Blueprint: cassandra-driver

Change-Id: I3ef827b069e578b664c483050c4b13e5d95f1f9b

commit_message:
Set pipefail when running tsfilter

The timestamp filter function pipes commands through awk to add
timestamps to those commands. We are interested in preserving the return
codes of those commands which requires pipefail. Set pipefail before
piping through awk then reset the old pipefail value after running
through awk.

Change-Id: I4e0ae2530669ec065a6cb78446cd27449beaeba9

commit_message:
Add UEFI support to ISO

* In UEFI bootloader is grub, not syslinux
* Removed mkisofs
* Removed isohybrid
* Add xorriso

Change-Id: I9158e939f388ef2000f898de4aed7f251202f6bd
Closes-Bug: #1433521

commit_message:
colorize osbash scripts using lib-color.sh

It colorizes the output of osbash.sh using
the conventions given in lib-color.sh.

Implements: blueprint osbash-color-support
Closes-Bug: #1443136
Change-Id: I42ca96454fdab47b283222e2deaf3e9b51d03106

[{'created': '2015-05-08 16:13:26.000000000', 'message': "Add OpenStack logo in the footer

- add small transparent OpenStack logo in the slide footer
- logo and footer design is from OpenStack's
  OpenStackPowered-April2015.ppt master slides
- white background changed to transparent

commit_message:
Add OpenStack logo in the footer

- add small transparent OpenStack logo in the slide footer
- logo and footer design is from OpenStack's
  OpenStackPowered-April2015.ppt master slides
- white background changed to transparent
- logo is pushed back with z-index: -2 (so it is behind background pic
  in the title slide)

Change-Id: Iccdd9a968816f00dde60230df45c5a21d212d38e

commit_message:
Provide a longer timeout for HA scenario

HA Scenarios (3 controllers + 1 Node) may require more than 35 minutes
to run, hence increase the scenario timeout.

Change-Id: Ia68fee38f99dba18badc07eb0adbc473cfcffdf3

commit_message:
Dell: Added support for update_migrated_volume

Added support for updated_migrated_volume to common driver.
Added rename_volume to dell_storagecenter_api to support it.
Added tests to test_dellsc.py and test_dellapi.py.

The only thing we do in this rename the newly migrated volume
destination volume on the Dell Storage center to be the same
as the original volume ID.  Since we identify the volumes
by volume ID this prevents them from being lost.

Change-Id: I531e24853cf5db8b7c34d91460d3abe786a652de
Closes-bug: 1452919

commit_message:
Hypervisor Support Matrix renders links in notes

The sphinx-extension which renders the support_matrix.ini file into
HTML did not recognize URLs in the notes which have to be written as
an HTML anchor element. This commit changes that. The links are
clickable now.

Closes-Bug: 1451468

Change-Id: Ia05610afb32c7a86536b7f462d3cfc44f9a2ca7d

commit_message:
Add new winimage-builder

* shell script based instead of make
* updated links on required software
* updated PowerShell unattended scripts
* updated autounattend & unattend xml templates files
* checked with Windows Server 2012 R2
* Windows 2008 R2 support - is not refactored(planned)

Change-Id: Id54c363e2c2f3d47f9b48c23a0368beec2fb6102

"}, {'created': '2015-05-13 17:55:28.000000000', 'message': 'Covered a bug in functional test infrastructure.

When api is launched with default flavor (no authentication) and
registry with fakeauth flavor (or any other requiring user token) any
CRUD operation via api without a valid token should return 401, as
long as the user receives 401 from glance registry.

But the expected behaviour is not observed with glance v2 api. The user
can still perform any operation without supplying a token in headers.

Change-Id: Iee9e9fc4a21ccc90489873b086beff68c730d38f
'}]
commit_message:
Covered a bug in functional test infrastructure.

When api is launched with default flavor (no authentication) and
registry with fakeauth flavor (or any other requiring user token) any
CRUD operation via api without a valid token should return 401, as
long as the user receives 401 from glance registry.

But the expected behaviour is not observed with glance v2 api. The user
can still perform any operation without supplying a token in headers.

Change-Id: Iee9e9fc4a21ccc90489873b086beff68c730d38f

[{'created': '2015-05-18 14:36:28.000000000', 'message': "Fix test test_cluster_locking_after_deployment

This fix does not solve the root cause of the problem,
deadlock with fake thread is still there, but proper
solution with correct lock ordering is huge, so we

commit_message:
Fix test test_cluster_locking_after_deployment

This fix does not solve the root cause of the problem,
deadlock with fake thread is still there, but proper
solution with correct lock ordering is huge, so we
won't be able to land it in 6.1, this patch fixes
the problem and lives logic of the tests as is.
As result it will be possible to make backports to
this branch without random test fails.

Change-Id: I7cf4c4ce0507afeda760fc1fbdeabac43b0e2909
Closes-bug: #1455467

commit_message:
objects: convert HVSpec to use named enums

The hv_type, vm_mode and arch fields in the HVSpec object all
accept a finite list of values, so should be represented by
an Enum field instead of String. This converts HVSpec to use
the existing ArchitectureField, and also defines VMModeField
and HVTypeField classes.

The hash of VirtCPUModel changes because the field classname
has changed from String to an enum type. The HVSpec objects
are populated based on data reported by the hypervisor
drivers. These are using the named constants and validation
code to ensure only well known values are recorded in the
data. So this change to an enum type should be ABI-compatible
and thus the version is not incremented.

Change-Id: Iffbc9bd3532e7bfbfe2aefee52621ceb3fb57f27

commit_message:
Fix two bugs in cluster resize

1. The parameter parsing of adjustment number should allow
   negative input value for scaling in scenario;
2. The desired value should be the sum of current and rounded
   when adjustment type is CHANGE_IN_PERCENTAGE.

Change-Id: Ib19d7a61c220ea61786acd078e5d3e329e3006dd

[{'created': '2015-05-17 17:49:07.000000000', 'message': 'Remove pacemaker haproxy resource (temporary)

Currently an issue with HAProxy pacemaker resource prevent the HA
deployment from working.

HAProxy can be started on all nodes (pcs resource create --clone), even
though the haproxy configuration is not written on the non
$pacemaker_master node. Since the VIP can be on any node, if the vip end
up in a non $pacemaker_master node then deployment will fail.

NOTE: This is temporary, it aims to validate that the review[1] including
the changes to the new version of puppet-pacemaker works.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/183103/

Change-Id: I378bbdf73404f7286be30f485f42188b2922a80b
'}]
commit_message:
Remove pacemaker haproxy resource (temporary)

Currently an issue with HAProxy pacemaker resource prevent the HA
deployment from working.

HAProxy can be started on all nodes (pcs resource create --clone), even
though the haproxy configuration is not written on the non
$pacemaker_master node. Since the VIP can be on any node, if the vip end
up in a non $pacemaker_master node then deployment will fail.

NOTE: This is temporary, it aims to validate that the review[1] including
the changes to the new version of puppet-pacemaker works.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/183103/

Change-Id: I378bbdf73404f7286be30f485f42188b2922a80b

commit_message:
Add url access verification that will setup network

Added command that will perform setup and teardown of
required networking configuration.

Network configuration will perform next things:

- set interface up if required
- create vlan tagged interface and set it up
- add required ipv4 settings for interface
- add default route

After verification teardown will be performed.
Teardown is best effort based - e.g we should not fail whole command
if we cant fully execute teardown.

Change-Id: I910c15c2b39a917eb8428bb69271b5dde364b639
Partial-Bug: 1439686

commit_message:
Decouple sync_db from manage_service and enabled

We want db_sync to run even though manage_service or enabled
can be set to False.

Change-Id: Ic3472ce6a6e704a2fa035df6e1c8866b8ea6bcbc
Closes-Bug: 1452278

commit_message:
objects: convert VirtCPUModel to use named enums

The VirtCPUModel class currently uses anonymous enums for a
number of fields. Since some of the same enums will be required
in other objects, convert them to named enums instead.

The import of nova.compute.arch and nova.compute.cpumodel is
a temporary state. The intention is that the constants in those
two modules actually get moved into the enum classes themselves
allowing the modules to be removed. This is to be done in a
later commit.

The hash of VirtCPUModel changes because the field classname
has changed. The version is not incremented though, because
this is an ABI-compatible change.

Change-Id: Id79793510e02d47f9ef377b7b3a9ffa08dff4a66

commit_message:
Fixing "report_tempest_results.py"

The script "report_tempest_results.py" doesn't work and constantly fails
with the following error:

    TypeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute '__getitem__'

This patch is entended to fix this issue.

Closes-Bug: #1456139

Change-Id: Iff3fdf198bcca71321522c5938b128995d0d6cea

commit_message:
Do not fail test on post snapshot creation step

If test passed, but creation of diagnostic snapshot
failed after test, then error is printed to console,
but test isn't marked as failed.

Change-Id: I5e3df9045900254538fe6ccd3b7334e75f5410ac
Closes-bug: #1455781

commit_message:
Set default Fuel Client commit to 6.1.0

Since versioning scheme of Fuel Client was changed
it's now necessary to specify the latest stable version
as the default one for building ISOs.

Change-Id: I23cb4f0825947e66986f39ec160787da4a6b44da

commit_message:
Move VersionedObject registration to the new scheme

In oslo.versionedobjects, objects are registered inside a separate
ObjectRegistry class. Each object is registered with a decorator
(with less magic). Also remove unused check_object_version method.

Related to blueprint versioned-objects

Change-Id: I0f9fd3fdaa754480ccd9e18b6c15501900aa46ee

commit_message:
Change default network mode for env creation to neutron

Now when user choses nova-network as network mode for environment
warning about deprecation is displayed. segmentation-type  parameter is
now also supplied by default and is equal to "vlan". Tests updated.

Change-Id: Idb1d5caac4f3e2c4d9661eb8162eaabefa4fca49
Closes-Bug: #1455739

Andrew, will the documentation be in this patch or a new one?'}, {'account_id': 8091, 'date': '2015-02-25 21:03:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

looking good so far, but see note on location of job_execution update and we have some things to decide:

URLs with placeholders can end up in job_configs as well, either by data_source reference substitution (handled in resolve_data_source_references() ) or by manual entry of a URL with placeholders in job_configs (an arg to a Java job, for example).  I think these should be resolved too.

If we fix up placeholders in job_configs, then we also need to do this in the Spark EDP engine, not just the Oozie engine.

We may want to consider refactoring run_job(). When I added data_source reference substitution, I did not want to change the signature of run_job, so I added substitution in both engines. Mostly I did not want to have "job_configs" passed in when job_execution already contains a job_configs field. I thought this might cause confusion.

But, if we consider passing more arguments to engine.run_job() we may be able to do all of the data_source reference and URL handling in one place in the job_manager before the call to run_job() instead of in each EDP engine. I think it is becoming complicated enough that we may want to do that.

Instead, we may want to create one consolidated routine in job_utils that handles all data_source and URL resolution to avoid duplication.  In this case, the new code added to the Oozie engine would be somehow combined with resolve_data_source_references(). But this may end up being a big routine.

Thoughts?'}, {'account_id': 8091, 'date': '2015-02-25 21:07:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Note that FrozenClass errors keep us from modifying job_execution itself before passing it to run_job().

I have often wanted a method that would give me an editable object version of job_execution, a full copy, so that for instance job_execution.job_configs could be altered in place before run_job()

If we follow the convention that no database updates happen in the EDP engines, then operating on this copy would be fine. Maybe we should consider this.'}, {'account_id': 8091, 'date': '2015-02-25 21:18:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Hmm, maybe it's not so bad.  Maybe the job_configs issues can be fixed up by simply calling 

job_utils.construct_data_source_url(
                data_source, job_execution)

For each substituted URL in resolve_data_source_references() instead of just copying the URL"}, {'account_id': 8411, 'date': '2015-02-25 21:21:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Mike I think in the next. The feature is fully backward compatible. No harm in having it undocumented for some time.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-02-25 21:46:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Implemented support of placeholders in datasource URLs

Added ability to use placeholders in datasource URLs. Currently
supported placeholders:
* %RANDSTR(len)% - will be replaced with random string of
  lowercase letters of length `len`.
* %JOB_EXEC_ID% - will be replaced with the job execution ID.

Resulting URLs will be stored in a new field at job_execution
table. Using 'info' field doesn't look as good solution since it
is reserved for oozie status.

Next steps:
* write documentation
* update horizon

Implements blueprint: edp-datasource-placeholders

Change-Id: I1d9282b210047982c062b24bd03cf2331ab7599e

commit_message:
Fix cluster templates update

This change fixes the following issues:

* Remove _appy_defaults for cluster template fields on update
  Fields that are not specified should not be given default values
  on update like they are on creation.  If a field is not specified,
  it should be left alone

* Do not delete node groups if the cluster template update does
  specify a node_group field

Closes-Bug: #1438077
Change-Id: I65dd15e02871f9c7227d2b51acedd6e06cb04950

commit_message:
Prevented failed nodes from being rebooted

Provision fault tolerance makes it possible
to continue deployment even if some of nodes
failed while being provisioned. But if
reboot such failed node with chain loader
it likely can stick on this stage and we won't
be able to reboot it any way except turning it off
and on.

This change prevents failed nodes from being rebooted
with chain loader. Besides this patch sets
profile for IBP nodes into 'bootstrap', so as to
avoid them being booted with anaconda or debian-installer.

Change-Id: Id2b500d359fa2772ef0a81bef37f2f7152894b00
Closes-Bug: #1455385

commit_message:
Install Oozie UI on MapR clusters

It's needed to rebuild Oozie war with ExtJS archive
specified to make Oozie UI work. Note that we have
to rebuild it every time configure.sh runs on Oozie
node because script rebuilds it w/o ExtJS.

Closes-Bug: #1439452
Change-Id: I14e2c6742913898f3a129d4423c8cbf2be8f7632
(cherry picked from commit 06905eac10fc81f8b887a53ca0893382481dad32)

commit_message:
Change augtool invocation

- Change autosave mode to configuration file mode, because
  in Precise augtool return wrong value with augtool -s command.
- Add -e flag, and now it not trigger any dib-lint error

Change-Id: I239d403d1c20782525766c67b139e40c00907792
Closes-Bug: #1450510
Partial-Bug: #1435306

commit_message:
Force tagging on docker restore

Docker refuses to allow latest tags to be written
if there is already a newer latest tag without
-f option.

Change-Id: I72e9e3addff6f2be5b66dc18d3162c19045c4e47
Closes-Bug: #1448211

Need to pass correct int value for provisioned_capacity_gb capability
to get it working with scheduler.

commit_message:
Added xz package to shotgun spec

That is for making it possible to use xz for
compressing diagnostic snapshot instead of gzip.
It gonna take twice as less place as gzip one.

Related fuel-web patch: Ia8ba5d584ea97de4f476cb8bb632ca82baa76503

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1394487

Change-Id: Ia35fb7294c85d0463860ca8af9812834522f5605

commit_message:
Add EDITOR variable in urlaccesschecker

This variable required by cmd2 library to work.
Without - it fails on bootstrap with traceback:

File "/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/cmd2.py", line 424, in Cmd
if subprocess.Popen(['which', editor])

Change-Id: I061f88b65d7bc7181752cd076da4067df2f84131
Related-Bug: 1439686

commit_message:
Change an IPMI meter name

Change "hardware.ipmi.node.inlet.temperature"
meter name to "harware.ipmi.node.temperature".
The change is according to ceilometer service.
Please reference:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/170379.

Closes-Bug: #1455335

Edits VMware issues in user-side docs for 6.1

Some issues related to VMware technologies
are outdated.
You can find the list of all issues
in the bug description.

All changes will be made to Planning and User Guides.

commit_message:
Check if nodes are able to connect to ubuntu repos

 * Add CheckNodesToRepositoryConnectionTask
 * Add above task call to ApplyChangesTaskManager
 * Add repo_connection_resp to to receiver
 * Add process synchronization by barrier
 * Make ApplyChangesTaskManager wait for new subtask using barrier
 * Add new fake task type for execute_shell astute action

Change-Id: I3c13afc0a1cef42efd42f26d7593ada8c3ce44c4
Depends-On: Ie507f695644237f1a1a8f3b6d212d236a3ab317d
Closes-Bug: #1439686

(1 comment)

I can not say that this patch is fully useful, and the implementation takes the right place, in my opinion. Let me explain briefly, feel free to follow up with me and discuss it in more details. Two use cases:
1) this case verifies only connectivity before provisioning run. In majority of the cases, it would not be a problem: default gw is master node, which will have Internet in majority of the cases.
2) another case is when node is provisioned, and then l23network ran. After it, your default gw will change to the one defined on Network settings tab. Deployment will fail with unclear message (some issue with apt using IPv6), which is actually masking of real issue with absent connectivity.

Use case #1 could be easily covered by network checker, which could just try to ping 8.8.8.8. For the use case #2 it's pretty hard to extend net-checker, as we would need to configure network in the same way as l23network would do. Anyway, I'm in favor of extending network checker for both use cases. Please talk to Lukasz or Dmitry Shulyak about network checker."}, {'account_id': 13445, 'date': '2015-05-05 06:30:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-05 06:55:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10:

@Mike: what about the case when we are provisioning Ubuntu nodes (not in IBP) and they don't have access to repositories (not necessarily in the internet)?

I believe that provisioning can't be successful in that case.

From my conversations with bug reporter I gathered that it was acceptable to make this check before provisioning, because the bug was about checking if Ubuntu provisioning will be possible.

I think it would be good to add the check for provisioning type - if it's IBP, check should not be performed.

I think your comment is valid, but maybe it should be done in another bug/change, as the scope of the problem you are referring to is slightly different?"}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:05:59.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 11.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:06:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- noop http://logs.openstack.org/54/172954/11/check/noop/5586efc/ : SUCCESS'}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:11:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 6623, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:55:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11:

(1 comment)

One concern inline, otherwise lgtm.'}, {'account_id': 6623, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:55:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: Code-Review-1

Forgot to put the score'}, {'account_id': 14840, 'date': '2015-05-05 09:56:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11: Code-Review+1

I disagree with Mike on case #1:

User can provide his own local mirrors as repositories. And nodes could not have an internet connectivity at all.
So this check is quite useful.

As for case #2 - that's true. We have nothing to do with it within this patchset."}, {'account_id': 13948, 'date': '2015-05-05 10:11:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 6623, 'date': '2015-05-05 10:36:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

(1 comment)

Guys, thank you for your responses. I left another comment inline.

@Mike, I aree that it's possible to check this by the network checker. However, it doesn't look to me like checking whether repositories are available (by downloading Release) files is something that should be inside a low-level network checker. Btw, having this check inside a python tool would resolve my concern I mentioned inline easily :)

After the provisioning it is necessary to do a different kind of check not by using a netchecker or wget but by using apt-check (or something like that) in order to be sure that all repos are functional."}, {'account_id': 8797, 'date': '2015-05-05 19:29:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

What do we need to do this for, if we are using classic or IBP, all of the nodes have the fuel master as their gateway, in this case we only need to validate access on the master node as we should expect implicit success.

This appears to only be running in one of the two modes, both need the access test

[note] This doesn't fix the fact that the network will be reconfigured by l23network later and will go through a different path from discovery. We will need an additional test."}, {'account_id': 8797, 'date': '2015-05-05 19:30:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

CentOS has repo's too and should also be accounted for in the test"}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-06 08:10:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 11:

@Andrew: if you are right this doesn't really make sense. I will double check this and move this check to nailgun if necessary.

About your sidenote: I saw you already started working on it: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/180345/1 . Will it be enough to ensure that slave nodes have connection to repositories?"}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-06 08:18:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11:

About checking only on native provisioning - I thought that IBP provides the system to slave nodes without any need for repository connection on their side. Am I wrong?'}, {'account_id': 14543, 'date': '2015-05-18 08:47:32.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Check if Ubuntu nodes can access repositories

Before provisioning there is an additional check - all nodes that have
provile that contains 'ubuntu' (assumption is that they are indeed
Ubuntu nodes) are trying to get 'Release' file from all their
repositiories to make sure that installation will fail due to lack of
access to needed packages.

Wget is used to check ability to retrieve files from repositories. It is
invoked on nodes via MCollective agent action 'execute_shell_command'.

Also added pry to developer dependencies.

Closes-Bug: #1439686

commit_message:
Adding dpkg-dev to required CentOS packages

After dpkg-devel upgraded to dpkg-devel-1.16.16-5.el6.x86_64 there was
no longer dpkg-scanpackages command available on the machine until
installing dpkg-dev-1.16.16-5.el6.noarch.

Before installing dpkg-dev, the plugin build crashed because
dpkg-scanpackages is a required command in order to build a fuel plugin.

Closes-bug: #1455882

Change-Id: I588ce4291b03c7cec27c3dfbac350575aa1699b4

commit_message:
Respect configured cred provider in scenario utils

This commit fixes the scenario util classes to actually used the
configured credential provider. Previously these classes were making
a bare call to Manager() to setup the clients. However without passing
it credentials to use Manager tries to use credentials from the config
file regardless of whether tempest is configured using the old config
options for credentials. (it ignores the accounts.yaml or tenant
isolation settings)

Closes-Bug: #1451484
Change-Id: Ie3bca345e094c00299167d37150cca3d6c1d8b38

commit_message:
Fix appearing an error message when build Storm with other than Ubuntu

Storm doesnt support other than Ubuntu.
If base_image_os is selected Fedora or CentOS,
appear an error message instead of building Storm with Ubuntu.

Change-Id: Icfa07ab764b69e19423065061d88ee4079fb66a4
Closes-Bug: #1441589

commit_message:
Add support for overriding cache just for seed

When testing with the seed as the undercloud, I'm frequently wanting
to rebuild just the seed VM image, e.g when I know the overcloud images
are good, but I want to test a new heat patch.

This adds support for SEED_USE_CACHE, which will override the global
USE_CACHE variable if set.

Change-Id: I81f256feedbee26a258333a68bf8715bbc7710bf

commit_message:
Use Keystone V3 API openstack role list --group

Devstack functions-common::get_or_add_group_project_role uses
--group options, which only exists in Keystone V3 API. Howere here
the python-openstackclietn defaults to use V2 API, triggers
"unrecognized arguments: --group" error.

This patch fixes the bug by forcing openstack client to use V3 API.
The existing functions-common::get_or_create_group are already
using the same way. See

https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/functions-common#L678

Change-Id: I6a60c88a90958f2a95da383d45a80db9b5c02d7e
Closes-bug: #1441010

Instead of creating an empty TenantTopology object every time you try
and get a tenant it will only do it where one doesn't already exist. By
still using dict.setdefault() we keep it thread safe for the corner
cases.

Change-Id: Ie754482ef1b9585251ebd887c434dcb1ea038853
"}, {'created': '2015-05-18 07:01:23.000000000', 'message': "Optimized get_tenant_by_id()

Instead of creating an empty TenantTopology object every time you try
and get a tenant it will only do it where one doesn't already exist. By

commit_message:
Optimized get_tenant_by_id()

Instead of creating an empty TenantTopology object every time you try
and get a tenant it will only do it where one doesn't already exist. By
still using dict.setdefault() we keep it thread safe for the corner
cases.

Change-Id: Ie754482ef1b9585251ebd887c434dcb1ea038853

commit_message:
Fix kill for rabbit OCF

* There is undefined stop_pid argument could be
passed to the kill command for some cases when rabbit
app cannot be stopped gracefully. Renamed to pid.
* There is also unnecessary "kill" code duplication exist
and is removed.
* The pid value passed for the kill command is now always
verified to be not empty.

Closes-bug: #1455880

Change-Id: I0af8e275873c08fd44d3fc3abf40b7e99674986d
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Handle optional dependency in vmware store

oslo_vmware is an optional dependency for glance_store. Hence, we
should be able to register the store options even if the library
is not installed. There are two problems addressed here :-
1. The import error was not handled.
2. One of the store opt referenced a constant from the library.

commit_message:
Remove size related parameters from cluster updating

Now we don't allow to update size related properties of cluster, e.g.
min_size, max_size, desired_capacity. These properties can only be
changed using cluster resizing

Change-Id: I0f1c1c866d41ae5b9e99005b7946ccc635749c77

commit_message:
Only clone tempest with depth of 1

For automation, there's usually no need to clone the entire
revision history.

Change-Id: I766fc0ef100376578daac985cb7a85a9a07dd6ed
Closes-Bug: #1455240

commit_message:
Updating Alice's case studies on Management

Adding new section on management touching on:
+ Repository for baseline configurations not captured in golden images
+ Update and patching policy is created
+ Out-of-band management configurations called out
+ Golden image management is outlined

Change-Id: Ib3d1fe9632437107043677afcfe98ab03ac1d578
Partial-Bug: #1349540

commit_message:
Updating Alice's case study for Networking

+ Updating Alice's case study focusing on nova-network
+ Noting that she will eventually migrate to Neutron (and why she chose
nova-network now)
+ Broke second sentence into three for readability
+ Clarified use of 'with' VLAN Manager
+ Updated OpenStack Networking (neutron) per convention
+ Added a missing word in second sentence
+ Updated VLAN network manager per convention

Change-Id: If6b3a073b7f5ee22267cd29d48b5c510edb1338f
Partial-Bug: #1349540

commit_message:
Updating Alice's case studies for intro, communication, and docs

Updating the Alice case studies for introduction, secure communication,
and system documentation sections. This outlines a more specific and
more comprehensive case study as well as ensuring consistency for
the examples and compliance standard used. Adding RC4 algorithm to
the not recommended list, and updating per doc conventions.

Change-Id: I29bb509254d5b55e01c2c92fe37b6d04f9f02585
Partial-Bug: #1349540

commit_message:
Add support of container resource management with "name"

This patch supports magnum container resource related
commands to run with name of the resource also.
Below is the list of commands:
 - container-delete
 - container-show
 - container-reboot
 - container-stop
 - container-start
 - container-pause
 - container-unpause
 - container-logs
 - container-execute

Change-Id: I4aaa1346a9411a8d0a9088c8fb216ee36df90915
Partially-Implements: blueprint name-based-resource-management

do off_by_default checks not run at all? or run and get ignored? That will be important in evaluating what can be added here.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2015-05-11 15:04:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

Should not be executed at all.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-05-12 21:04:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

The machinery that pep8 exposes to us makes it kind of difficult to arbitrarily silence things, so I implemented "off by default" as an addition to the list of ignored error/warning codes. They're always loaded because they're registered as entry-points like other extensions though.

That said, what actually runs checks is pep8 and I'm fairly confident that pep8 will run every check across the source and only report things that are either in the select list or (if select is not provided) not in the ignore list. I could be mistaken about that though.'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2015-05-13 00:13:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13: Code-Review-1

of requiring all of the projects to change to adhere to the

commit_message:
Add support for flake8 off_by_default for optional checks

This allows hacking checks to be added as optional which means
that they are assumed to be excluded and have to be explicitly
added as part of a 'select' entry in the [flake8]
stanza of tox.ini.

The goal is to allow checks to be staged into the projects instead
of requiring all of the projects to change to adhere to the
check prior to the check being added (which creates a window where
failing code could be added).  Instead checks can be staged in with
enforcement and once all (or the majority) of projects have enabled
it, the check can be changed to a required check.

One optional check is added as an example:
  H106: Don't put vim configuration in source files

Depends-On: I7f8ef22254703a53b73ccd048322191cfc677958
Change-Id: If188f85e8093974802bd2bacc2a72b2ae35ee5a1

commit_message:
Fix chainloading iPXE (undionly.kpxe)

This patch is making the neutron DHCP provider to explicitly check if
the request is coming from iPXE before ACK'ing the PXE request with the
iPXE script (When iPXE is enabled only).

Also, update the documentation that explains how to configure neutron
for iPXE to create the "ipxe" tag based on the DHCP user class or DHCP
option 175 (as before).

Change-Id: I60f9f515a9bd45aed6b2f6f9165a2f85259b3879
Closes-Bug: #1454332

commit_message:
Reduce AMT Driver's dependence on new release of Openwsman

As Openwsman>=2.4.10 is not widely supported so far, like Ubuntu.
Reduce AMT Driver's dependence on the new release of Openwsman to become
more user friendly.

Specifically, this enables setting the boot device even with Openwsman v2.4.3

Change-Id: I52c67cd9aa3b1693375e95ee1a582a08623308a9
Close-Bug: #1454018

commit_message:
Add volume status to error messages in backup create flow

If volume status is not 'available' we can't create a backup. Adding
current volume status to error message will make logs more
user-friendly.

Change-Id: Iab7a794a5104b28c54de23571f589fcf60e09c7d

commit_message:
supports alembic migration for db2

This patch adds the optional runtime dependency to support db2
for alembic migration, will not break the default mysql path.

And I did the testing in db2 env, works fine.

Change-Id: I59deff0d82bc9e2e7ceaa157c626cd2bb7a36f0d
Closes-Bug: 1444270
(cherry picked from commit a4ade0beaa196db26595301b9692d6236af61709)

commit_message:
pagination info at top and bottom of table

Pagination info at top and bottom of any horizon table.
For instance, by default, you typically limit table size to 20 but only display
that there are more than 20 returned entities at the bottom of a page.
Good ux design principles require that you display this at top and
bottom of a page.
And that you be able to go to the next "n" entries from the top or
bottom via a navigator button.

Change-Id: I68b077042b0781845d27b26708c702b6c9dfba26
Closes-Bug: #1359238
Signed-off-by: Kuo-tung Kao <jelly.k@inwinstack.com>

commit_message:
pagination info at top and bottom of table

Pagination info at top and bottom of any horizon table.
For instance, by default, you typically limit table size to 20 but only display
that there are more than 20 returned entities at the bottom of a page.
Good ux design principles require that you display this at top and
bottom of a page.
And that you be able to go to the next "n" entries from the top or
bottom via a navigator button.

Fix the test code.

Beofre:
The number of '<th' is  7 + 1
1 for button column
7 for the column of pagination info.

After:
The number of '<th' is  7 + 7 + 1
1 for button column
7 for the top column of pagination info.
7 for the bottom column of pagination info.

Change-Id: Ie3a459ef1198cd7e5cfa50d4340840d10846818f
Closes-Bug: #1359238
Signed-off-by: Kuo-tung Kao <jelly.k@inwinstack.com>

commit_message:
Don't set tempest fixed_network_name with neutron

If neutron is enabled then there isn't a shared private network
between all tenants which is what is required for the
fixed_network_name config option. This commit adds a conditional
to not set that option when neutron is enabled. While not necessarily
fatal to tempest it does emit a warning on almost every server create
call if it is set with a non-existent network name.

Change-Id: I1a42fa6b0b5a93b411c08ec35df043d6ea69d453

commit_message:
Disable propagating BadStoreConfiguration

Commit I1d4f95cba47d21f1eb7e580314d01ac8d3481586 propergates
BadStoreConfiguration to the consumer of glance_store. This breaks
backwards compatibility for existing glance installations, however. This
patch disables it for the time being.

Change-Id: I46e1e38bf0b3ba9f78b4e553178b49bee929e0fd

commit_message:
Add release notes for 0.18.0

Changes included in this release:

    $ git log 0.17.0..0.18.0 --no-merges --oneline
    8b4456a Uncap library requirements for liberty
    76c9f68 Add unit tests for log_curl_request
    bd0aa06 Fix https stack trace on python 3.4 client
    c698b4e Fix client when using no ssl compression
    64a1a0f Add SSL cert verification regression tests
    c730266 Omit 'locations' as image-create parameter
    a6234d1 Creating task with invalid property crashes in py3
    fd2f989 Don't accept *args for client
    e386e44 Stub authentication requests rather than plugins
    27f70bb Remove keystoneclient mocks
    02b1a05 Replace mox in tests with requests-mock
    90407d9 Expose 'is_base' schema property attribute
    2c08b40 Validate tag name when filtering for images
    13b5a5a Remove redundant FakeSchemaAPI __init__ method
    c149a94 glance image-show now have --human-readable option
    42d7548 Test unit for checking update active images
    6d864ef Correct help messages for image-update command
    f272ab3 Generate API documentation
    a1bb3eb Use any instead of False in generator

Change-Id: I687bef82afd7bb9a379297d7128a009cc051ca75

commit_message:
Enable netfilter on bridges

There is a long-standing issue with netfilter enablement on bridges
which differs across distributions.  For some history see [1]

Neutron requires this enabled as documented in [2].  This change
allows centos7+neutron to pass the security group tests in tempest.

I will investigate why neutron can't do this itself.  Ubuntu don't
notice because their defaults are on.  Other than the documentation
change in [2], it seems we also work around this in other deployment
methods (e.g. packstack with
Ia8c86dcb31810a8d6b133a161388604fde9bead4).

[1] http://wiki.libvirt.org/page/Net.bridge-nf-call_and_sysctl.conf
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/icehouse/install-guide/install/apt/content/neutron-ml2-network-node.html

Change-Id: I4ee1a34c2549eddbdd32d67059dad7af0cae48e0

commit_message:
Fix Python versions supported

We have CI for 2.6, 2.7, 3.4. So make sure
all references to other versions are removed and
all 3 versions above are correctly mentioned where
required.

Make sure we specify 3.4 everywhere needed

Change-Id: I2c90bccfc7495bf8197319196a12b2a8bd0519f1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-05-06 09:17:21.000000000', 'message': "rabbit: fixes a logging issue

When uses the default port, kombu.Connection.port is None

So we replace the usage of kombu.Connection.port per
kombu.Connection.info(), to get the default value.

Also some transport driver have 'None' for hostname or port as default
value, so replace usage of '%d' per '%s', to ensure the logging never fail.
Event the output of the log is less sexy.

Change-Id: I89ca1982246146717015253bd4cc26f992381584
Closes-bug: #1452189
"}]
commit_message:
rabbit: fixes a logging issue

When uses the default port, kombu.Connection.port is None

So we replace the usage of kombu.Connection.port per
kombu.Connection.info(), to get the default value.

Also some transport driver have 'None' for hostname or port as default
value, so replace usage of '%d' per '%s', to ensure the logging never fail.
Event the output of the log is less sexy.

Change-Id: I89ca1982246146717015253bd4cc26f992381584
Closes-bug: #1452189

commit_message:
Check whether to recreate service if it exists

    The create_service action only checks to see if a service
    with the same uuid exists, and if it does, it skips.  This
    addition checks to see whether a service matches the fields
    and deletes + recreates if fields need to be updated.

    Also included the specs for the ne functionality.

    It looks like the create_endpoint action already does this.
    Used the same process for checking the service.

Change-Id: I2013877f2f47096324386645f373690f5d9af4f5
Closes-Bug: #1306501
Closes-Bug: #1454022

commit_message:
Find resource refactoring

The 'name' field for some resources is called something different,
for example 'display_name' for volumes, 'name' for  volumes type.
So class 'resource' has attribute 'NAME_ATTR' wich contains
attribute name for different resources.

This change removes reduntant call find in resource manager, instead
of it checks NAME_ATTR value.

Related-Bug: #1449444
Change-Id: Ide334d7535c73cbdff72c30319eb539d8f5304d6

[{'created': '2015-05-15 12:59:02.000000000', 'message': 'Catch client exceptions during list ops

We were not consistently catching the underlying client exceptions
from the list operations, and just letting them escape as non-wrapped
exceptions. This corrects that.

Also, list_images() was trying to catch an OpenStackCloudException
that was never going to happen from the code in the try block.

Change-Id: Ia863ec2f988c7e90138097be15cd66fc858d1b21
'}]
commit_message:
Catch client exceptions during list ops

We were not consistently catching the underlying client exceptions
from the list operations, and just letting them escape as non-wrapped
exceptions. This corrects that.

Also, list_images() was trying to catch an OpenStackCloudException
that was never going to happen from the code in the try block.

Change-Id: Ia863ec2f988c7e90138097be15cd66fc858d1b21

Remove zuul-cloner workaround for DIB

We added this to work around a bug in zuul-cloner, but the bug is now
fixed.

commit_message:
set up skeleton files for ha-guide

This commit creates content-free files.  After it is merged,
we can proceed to add content in separate commits.

All pathnames use hyphens as the space delimiter.

Implements blueprint improve-ha-guide

Change-Id: I87a078883680b2e40959279e29c2d427131097ce

commit_message:
[install-guide] Ubuntu release package updates

Update the following items for the Ubuntu release packages
(2015.1):

1) Use RabbitMQ packages from the cloud archive repository.

2) Change default role from '_member_' to 'user' to avoid
   potential interference with an internal role.

3) Remove explicit configuration of 'log_dir' option in
   keystone.

4) Remove step to disable default host in Apache.

5) Update CirrOS image to 0.3.4.

Some of these changes apply to all distributions.

Change-Id: If1cdf839ebdc7655b89ab14df694a9c25f0c35cf
Implements: blueprint installguide-kilo

commit_message:
Fix event handler NotFound error

When an instance is destroyed, it is stopped first. The manager
will get the event and consider it an unexpected power off, so
it will try to call the stop API as well.

Meanwhile, the instance might be deleted, in which case the above
operation will fail with an "NotFound" error.

This can be avoided by catching this in the power off method.

(cherry picked from commit e6f864841b02bb9637e95bc08c36c812052d0d55)

Change-Id: Ibd173bfb6cefa7cd585eee2ff48b583841b1c05c

[{'created': '2015-05-17 17:54:34.000000000', 'message': "Fix serial console handler cleanup

The named pipe handler stop method checks if the 'stopped' event
was set before attempting to perform cleanup. The issue is if one
worker fails, it will set this event, preventing the stop method
from performing the cleanup.

In this case, the VM console log files will remain open, unable to
be deleted when the VM is destroyed.

This check can be safely removed.

The serial console handler is now stopped in case some workers
fail to start, avoiding the above mentioned situation.

(cherry picked from commit f01e14de9a251643ee172f98b90a3a83db1c24b4)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix serial console handler cleanup

The named pipe handler stop method checks if the 'stopped' event
was set before attempting to perform cleanup. The issue is if one
worker fails, it will set this event, preventing the stop method
from performing the cleanup.

In this case, the VM console log files will remain open, unable to
be deleted when the VM is destroyed.

This check can be safely removed.

The serial console handler is now stopped in case some workers
fail to start, avoiding the above mentioned situation.

Change-Id: I6b431cc530b87defeb0b10e1886f030a452b4b06
(cherry picked from commit f01e14de9a251643ee172f98b90a3a83db1c24b4)

commit_message:
Fix serial console handler cleanup

The named pipe handler stop method checks if the 'stopped' event
was set before attempting to perform cleanup. The issue is if one
worker fails, it will set this event, preventing the stop method
from performing the cleanup.

In this case, the VM console log files will remain open, unable to
be deleted when the VM is destroyed.

This check can be safely removed.

The serial console handler is now stopped in case some workers
fail to start, avoiding the above mentioned situation.

Change-Id: I6b431cc530b87defeb0b10e1886f030a452b4b06

commit_message:
Fix event handler NotFound error

When an instance is destroyed, it is stopped first. The manager
will get the event and consider it an unexpected power off, so
it will try to call the stop API as well.

Meanwhile, the instance might be deleted, in which case the above
operation will fail with an "NotFound" error.

This can be avoided by catching this in the power off method.

Change-Id: Ibd173bfb6cefa7cd585eee2ff48b583841b1c05c

commit_message:
Update IPv6 Prefix Delegation spec to include pluggable framework

Adds clarification that the PD client framework should be pluggable
to allow for different clients to be used in the future. Includes
some other small changes which better describe the Dibbler reference
implementation.

blueprint ipv6-prefix-delegation

Change-Id: Ice778a50ecff96ee663b83a477ff0f8bcf2ea745

commit_message:
Replace ci.o.o links with docs.o.o/infra

The http://ci.openstack.org/ documentation site has been deprecated,
replaced by redirects to corresponding paths within
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/ where other Project Infrastructure

WIP: Do not merge. Trying to figure out how to get rootwrap setup for

Closes-Bug: #1445052
"}, {'created': '2015-04-17 20:03:24.000000000', 'message': "VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit attempts to update the hook scripts for VPNaaS to use the
same/similar method as used with Neutron. The implication here, is that
instead of stacking with DevStack, we'll only set up the environment.

To pull this off, we install the neutron rootwrap commands and filters,
but place them in the VPN repo's .tox area. Next, DevStack is set up,
in the same manner as done with Neutron, except sudo is enabled on the
rootwrp commands in the VPN .tox area. Finally, VPN specific set ups
are done. This includes installing the IPSec package, configuring the
vpn_agent.ini file, and copying over rootwrap filters.

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052

"}, {'created': '2015-04-21 15:37:14.000000000', 'message': "VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit attempts to update the hook scripts for VPNaaS to use the
same/similar method as used with Neutron. The implication here, is that
instead of stacking with DevStack, we'll only set up the environment.

A new script is created to allow both the gate job and manual invocation
to set up for functional testing. First, the script sources the Neutron
configure_for_func_testing.sh script to configure devstack environment.

For this commit, a modified version of the Neutron script is used,
because a different path is needed for rootwrap sudoer. Future commits
will remove this duplication in the two repos, so that the Neutron
version can be used by VPNaaS (and other services).

Next, the script will install the IPSec package, based on the functional
job, and will create the vpn_agent.ini file, in case it is needed for
tests.

To configure the environment manually, one can do:
    tools/configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh \
        <parent-dir> <func-job-name> <devstack-repo> [-i]

where:
   parent-dir...... is the path to the parent of this repo (would be
                    /opt/stack/new when run by gate)
   func-gate-name.. Either dsvm-functional or dsvm-functional-sswan
   devstack-repo... Path to devstack repo (/opt/stack/new/devstack
                    when run by gate)
   -i.............. Indicates to install Neutron package dependencies

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052
Depends-On: Ie44e45c117bd864538e7919dfcf499091fde7752

"}, {'created': '2015-05-02 16:22:59.000000000', 'message': 'VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit attempts to update the hook scripts for VPNaaS to use the
same/similar method as used with Neutron. The implication here, is that
instead of stacking with DevStack, we'll only set up the environment.

A new script is created to allow both the gate job and manual invocation
to set up for functional testing. First, the script sources the Neutron
configure_for_func_testing.sh script to configure devstack environment.

For this commit, a modified version of the Neutron script placed in the
tools directory, is used, because a different path is needed for rootwrap
sudoer. Once [1] is upstreamed, this temp script can be removed.

Next, the script will install the IPSec package, based on the functional
job, will create the vpn_agent.ini file, in case it is needed for
tests, and will create a modified rootwrap filter that points to the
.tox area for testing.

For the neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script that is used for StrongSwan,
which uses a default config file in /etc/neutron (I could not figure
out how to override that CLI arg), the rootwrap.conf file from the .tox
area is copied to /etc/neutron/. Although as hackish way to set this, it
should work fine even for multiple jobs running in parallel, as the same
filter files and configuration settings are used for all jobs.

I did try to modify the vpnaas.filters file to pass an arg that points
to the rootwrap.conf in the .tox area, but the script is not "seeing"
that argument, and only sees the user args passed in for the script.

The other alternative I considered, was to create a test version of the
netns_wrapper.py file, but I don't know how to set the default value for
the rootwrap.conf to point to the .tox area with the specific job name.
It could be hard-coded for the dsvm-functional-sswan job, but if tests
are added to the dsvm-functional job, then this would break (or multiple
scripts that are nearly identical, would be needed).

To configure the environment manually, one can do:
    tools/configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh \
        <func-job-name> <devstack-repo> [-i]

where:
   func-gate-name.. Either dsvm-functional or dsvm-functional-sswan
   devstack-repo... Path to devstack repo (/opt/stack/new/devstack
                    when run by gate)
   -i.............. Indicates to install Neutron package dependencies

Ref: [1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/176064/

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052
Depends-On: I450273036e938a4acc9a7bc1dc193a9c207b2d58
'}, {'created': '2015-05-04 12:41:37.000000000', 'message': 'VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit updates the hook scripts for VPNaaS to use the same/similar
method as used with Neutron, where instead of stacking with DevStack,
we'll only set up the environment.

A new script is created to allow both the gate job and manual invocation
to set up for functional testing. First, the script sources the Neutron
configure_for_func_testing.sh script to configure devstack environment.

For this commit, a modified version of the Neutron script placed in the
tools directory, is used, because a different path is needed for rootwrap
sudoer. Once [1] is upstreamed, this temp script can be removed.

Next, the script will install the IPSec package, based on the functional
job, will create the vpn_agent.ini file, in case it is needed for
tests, and will create a modified rootwrap filter that points to the
.tox area for testing.

For the neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script that is used for StrongSwan,
which uses a default config file in /etc/neutron, the rootwrap.conf file
from the .tox area is copied to /etc/neutron/. This is a simple approach
that will work when multiple jobs are running, as the same config is used.

I did try to modify the vpnaas.filters file to pass an arg that points
to the rootwrap.conf in the .tox area, but the script is not "seeing"
that argument, and only sees the user args passed in for the script.

Another alternative I considered, was to create a test version of the
netns_wrapper.py file, but I don't know how to set the default value for
the rootwrap.conf to point to the .tox area with the specific job name.
It could be hard-coded for the dsvm-functional-sswan job, but if tests
are added to the dsvm-functional job, then this would break (or multiple
scripts that are nearly identical, would be needed).

A third possible solution, which could be done in a follow-up commit (as
we need to get functional tests running w/o stacking ASAP), is to have
the VPN driver obtain the rootwrap.conf file from vpnagent.ini file, and
explicitly pass this into the neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script, along
with the --cmd, and --mount-paths args. The tests could override the config.
This would give a realistic way to customize the rootwrap settings (right
now, I don't see how the file can be overridden).

To configure the environment for local run of the functional test, one
can do:
    tools/configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh \
        <func-job-name> <devstack-repo> [-i]

where:
   func-gate-name.. Either dsvm-functional or dsvm-functional-sswan
   devstack-repo... Path to devstack repo (/opt/stack/new/devstack
                    when run by gate)
   -i.............. Indicates to install Neutron package dependencies

Ref: [1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/176064/

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052
Depends-On: I450273036e938a4acc9a7bc1dc193a9c207b2d58
'}, {'created': '2015-05-04 21:36:37.000000000', 'message': "VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit does several things to allow functional tests to run, using a
DevStack configuration, but without stacking.

First, the gate_hook.sh is modified to specified environment variables
needed for processing, and will call configure_vpn_for_func_testing.sh.

The new configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh script will first call the Neutron
configure_for_func_testing.sh script (as modified in [1]) to setup DevStack.
The script then installs the IPSec package, based on the functional job, and
will create the vpn_agent.ini file, in case it is needed for tests.

Minor changes are made to the post-test_hook.sh to indicate the location for
the Neutron and VPN repos.

Lastly, tox.ini is modified to place the rootwrap related files into the
virtual environment, copy in the VPN rootwrap filter, set up the rootwrap
commands, and copy the (customized) rootwrap.conf to /etc/neutron.

This last step is needed, because th neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script that
is (currently) used for StrongSwan, uses /etc/neutron/rootwrap.conf and
doesn't allow overriding. This copying is a simple approach that will work
when multiple functional jobs are running, as the same config is used.

As a future follow-up commit, we could look into modifying the VPN device
drivers to pass the full path to the rootwrap.conf as a argument to the
neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script (--rootwrap_config). The setting could
be added to the vpnagent.ini config file, available via config, to allow
this to be customized to something other than /etc/neutron (for production
use), and the functional tests could override it to point to the right
virtual environment.

To configure the environment for local run of the functional test, one
can do:
    tools/configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh <devstack-repo> [-i]

where:
   devstack-repo... Path to devstack repo (/opt/stack/new/devstack
                    when run by gate)
   -i.............. Indicates to install Neutron package dependencies

For StrongSwan, prefix the command with VENV=dsvm-functional-sswan

Ref: [1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/176064/

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052
Depends-On: I450273036e938a4acc9a7bc1dc193a9c207b2d58

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Revise functional test hooks

This commit does several things to allow functional tests to run, using a
DevStack configuration, but without stacking.

First, the gate_hook.sh is modified to specified environment variables
needed for processing, and will call configure_vpn_for_func_testing.sh.

The new configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh script will first call the Neutron
configure_for_func_testing.sh script (as modified in [1]) to setup DevStack.
The script then installs the IPSec package, based on the functional job, and
will create the vpn_agent.ini file, in case it is needed for tests.

Minor changes are made to the post-test_hook.sh to indicate the location for
the Neutron and VPN repos.

Lastly, tox.ini is modified to place the rootwrap related files into the
virtual environment, copy in the VPN rootwrap filter, set up the rootwrap
commands, and copy the (customized) rootwrap.conf to /etc/neutron.

This last step is needed, because the neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script that
is (currently) used for StrongSwan, uses /etc/neutron/rootwrap.conf and
doesn't allow overriding. This copying is a simple approach that will work
when multiple functional jobs are running, as the same config is used.

As a future follow-up commit, we could look into modifying the VPN device
drivers to pass the full path to the rootwrap.conf as a argument to the
neutron-vpn-netns-wrapper script (--rootwrap_config). The setting could
be added to the vpnagent.ini config file, available via config, to allow
this to be customized to something other than /etc/neutron (for production
use), and the functional tests could override it to point to the right
virtual environment.

To configure the environment for local run of the functional test, one
can do:
    tools/configure_for_vpn_func_testing.sh <devstack-repo> [-i]

where:
   devstack-repo... Path to devstack repo (/opt/stack/new/devstack
                    when run by gate)
   -i.............. Indicates to install Neutron package dependencies

For StrongSwan, prefix the command with VENV=dsvm-functional-sswan

Ref: [1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/176064/

Change-Id: I2243b06b3cdbb352dac7bc47d03c830efb87be3c
Closes-Bug: #1445052
Depends-On: Ie490e89c1a65e126ad0a57d062076e472762837e

Use format options for functional tests

Use the format options for functional tests so we can have more
assertEquals and less assertIn.

commit_message:
Move free disk space checker to package

Adds fuel upgrade config for monitd by putting
Puppet resources into nailgun::host.

New package fuel-notify adds configuration for
monitd and a default config for the application.

Change-Id: I4a5e63b64e7a6d662ebd1e0387c6a84d601b0ca5
Related-Bug: #1371757

commit_message:
Send correct message about failed provision node, fix node type detection

We use 'hook' role because we do not need to calculate
multirole progress. Also for provision we do need role
at all. But here we use DeploymentProxyReporter and
need role.

Fix node type detection: 'target\n' or 'target' should
be detected as 'target'

Change-Id: Ibb87bf4a0b0abdf5ad0d703bb40cc55ae8ce9104
Closes-Bug: #1455824
Closes-Bug: #1455883
Co-Authored-By: Vladimir Kozhukalov <vkozhukalov@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: ukasz Ole <loles@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Check volume_backend in retype

The retype command does not do any checking with the
filter scheduler and blindly sends a driver.retype call
to the backend.  This is bad, because the drivers
expect to receive type specifications that have been
checked by the filter-scheduler before being sent to them.

Most drivers just ignore invalid keys/capabilites, and only
check those keys that are valid for them.  They assume things
like volume_backend_name are correct, otherwise they wouldn't
have received the call.

This patch is a partial fix to at least filter/check on
volume_backend_name, and also to allow the filter to pass
if there is only a single service with the cinder-volume topic.

The full fix is to implement a check via the scheduler to verify
that what's being attempted is valid regardless of migration or not.

Change-Id: Iab27fc75db4b6f7c12f7d67ae1bbe331ac7680bc
Partial-Bug: #1452823

This patch implements tunable configuration parameters for keystone.conf
as follows:
 - keystone_conf_settings: the default settings implemented by the
   keystone role
 - keystone_conf_tunables: the attribute available to use for overriding
   default settings and implementing additional settings

An example of how the tunables may be used is in:
 - etc/openstack_deploy/conf.d/tunables.yml.example

In order to achieve this the jinja2 do extension is enabled and a task is
added to the keystone role to merge the tunables into the settings. The
configuration file is then output using a generic template which iterates
through the settings to construct the file appropriately.

commit_message:
[WIP] Implement tunable keystone configuration

This patch implements tunable configuration parameters for keystone.conf
as follows:
 - keystone_conf_settings: the default settings implemented by the
   keystone role
 - keystone_conf_tunables: the attribute available to use for overriding
   default settings and implementing additional settings

An example of how the tunables may be used is in:
 - etc/openstack_deploy/conf.d/tunables.yml.example

In order to achieve this the jinja2 do extension is enabled and a task is
added to the keystone role to merge the tunables into the settings. The
configuration file is then output using a generic template which iterates
through the settings to construct the file appropriately.

Implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration
Change-Id: Idc5070d4ef86e40c0dbee5a5e9556c2d16c8db57

commit_message:
acceptance: don't install erlang on RHEL

Puppet erlang module does not pin puppetlabs-apt so it will have
conflicts in other modules if we want to use it (since we try to not use
2.0.0 release).

Let's simplify acceptance tests in not using erlang module and be
consistent with all Puppet OpenStack modules tests.

Change-Id: I6c79968becc11a19bddd2cba5aedb663f4c80c61

commit_message:
Avoid hard-coded UUID in quickstart guide

The quickstart guide requires users to copy-and-paste UUIDs to a
command, which is not user-friendly. This commit walk-around it.

Change-Id: Ie9f9f5525d1a067f0d8ebfcbaeb1471f63a70faf
Closes-Bug: 1454414

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be

    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others

and terminate_connection.  These drivers also don't have iscsi_helper

We've kept all iscsi_helper specific code in the tgt helpers

class.  These were LIO specific calls and as a result when a

in place and there were no distros setting LIO as the default iscsi_helper,
it appears that this has changed however.

and keeps the base ISCSIDriver generic.  I've also added a test
case for this in the SolidFire driver because it's impacted by
this.

(cherry picked from commit 7095e1c5a7477ca77c8698d96a969a7d78090a18)
"}]
commit_message:
Remove iscsi_helper calls from base iscsi driver

There are a number of drivers that inherit from the base
iscsi driver, using the base implementation of initialize_connection
and terminate_connection.  These drivers also don't have iscsi_helper
defined.

We've kept all iscsi_helper specific code in the tgt helpers
themselves, or in the various versions of the LVM driver
which is where they belong.

Over time however there have been some iscsi_helper specific
calls that have crept in to the base volume.driver:ISCSIDriver
class.  These were LIO specific calls and as a result when a
configuration is set with multi-backend to use lioadm as the
target helper, or even if it's not used but the default iscsi_helper
is set to lioadm the initialize_connection and terminate_connection
calls will try and access the LIO specific calls and raise because
the drivers inheriting from this class don't have target_helper
members.

This went unnoticed mostly because there's no significant LIO testing
in place and there were no distros setting LIO as the default iscsi_helper,
it appears that this has changed however.

This patch moves the LIO specific calls back where they belong
and keeps the base ISCSIDriver generic.  I've also added a test
case for this in the SolidFire driver because it's impacted by
this.

Change-Id: Ibe010b62bb2518685753dd515326e56ffcc99cea
Closes-Bug: #1400804
(cherry picked from commit 7095e1c5a7477ca77c8698d96a969a7d78090a18)

commit_message:
Updating the maxconn value in the defaults section

Updating the maxconn value in the defaults section to not exceed the maxconn
value specified in the global section. In this case the maxconn value in both
sections is set to 4000

Change-Id: Ib56157636e5e98c3292f2bf2320b9a25d1a9d0e0
backport: none
Closes-Bug: #1455062

commit_message:
Remove the security_group param in create server api

There is no security_group parameter. All we need is
security_groups.

Closes Bug: #1454479

Change-Id: Iaf3c46f7363a3e52f6cd295f5995128be18d3fdf

You missed bringing in the license info for this. Also since this is going to go into the security-site repo later, I think we need to relicense it from Apache to CC-BY like the VMT process document (which came from our CC-BY licensed wiki site)... I expect more content coming in from the wiki, hence easier if we keep it all compatible.

If we can fire up a quick thread about this on the ML and get some loose consensus on the relicensing then let's add headers like the VMT process document has. If we can't, then we'll need Apache license headers for now until we can work it out amongst ourselves. Also as you're an HP employee you should probably add a copyright HP line on behalf of the HP authors. Others can propose copyright lines on behalf of their respective employers if they feel the need to do so.

Also (sorry to keep piling on), but if you can add links in your commit message to the original Git repositories this content came from, that will make it easier for me to graft in the original commit history when moving it to the security-site repo later. Thanks!!!"}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2015-05-15 18:45:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Looks great, just one problem with the copyrights. However, since we're in a hurry to have this published on security.openstack.org prior to upcoming conference presentations/summit discussions I'm not going to block the review on that. It can be corrected in subsequent commits as time allows.

Also the copyright line on the VMT process document needs similar fixing, so let's make a point to get all that straightened out soon after the summit before we split them both out to the new security-site repo."}, {'account_id': 7473, 'date': '2015-05-16 22:32:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Refactor SimpleHTTP daemon for parallel execution

* Remove timeout. SimpleHTTP Daemon will run as long as required.
* Define SIGTERM event with stop() function. This allows to shutdown
  server properly and remove pidfile.
* Add extra check whether port is already opened.
* Add extra check for stale pidfile.
* Create PID files in "/tmp/simple_http_daemon" rather than '/tmp'
* Cleanup simple_http_daemon in case of make failures.

Change-Id: I19a9764d5e08bf8745dca8077faf951fb83c14a0
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Specify min numbers of threads as 2 for keystone wsgi

* If we set num threads as 2 this helps to handle apache2 stop better on
  virtual instances.
* Fix linting

Closes-Bug: 1455389
Change-Id: I43b6733b3cd25e2987ecb8574cd7579f8490adc8
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Fix kilo publishing

Fix a problem in publishdocs.sh: The copying of draft to kilo
copied the files to publish-docs/kilo/draft instead of to
publish-docs/kilo/ since the directory existed already.

Make this robust, always create the directory and copy the content of
it. Also remove draft-index.html, we don't need it in the kilo
directory.

Change-Id: I63e633dd4ecd4fd6ada74ca312d8cb6cb6a8fc28

I think _detect_server_image_flavor() should do the correct thing or can be change to do the correct thing without a need to rebuild the server.'}, {'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2015-05-04 15:20:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

@Jordan So I'm pretty sure this is a real bug. It's a race in test execution order and caused by our server re-use for all the test methods in this test class. Most hypervisors don't support resize down, and those that do are often just pretending they are because you could easily shrink the guest to be smaller than what's required to run it. That being said this just results in an extra server being created which I think is a fine trade off.

However, the more I look at this test class I think the "real" fix is to just move the resize test methods (and probably rebuild) into a separate file/test class which doesn't have any server reuse. The other actions being tested don't really alter the tests in a major way (well except for rebuild) so reuse is fine. But when we start changing what the server is made of reusing it gets a bit dirtier.

I did leave an inline comment on how we could continue to reuse the same test class if we wanted to. But, I'm not sure further increasing code complexity for the performance optimization of not creating an additional 4-6 servers is really worth it.'}, {'account_id': 6589, 'date': '2015-05-04 22:05:27.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-05 00:10:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Delete server after resize test

Explicitly deleting will prevent attempting to resize down an instance
that was used for other resize tests. Every resize test will get its own
server.

Because there is now no potential to be resizing back and forth between
flavor_ref and flavor_ref_alt we can do away with the code that tried to
figure out what the direction should be. Resizes will now always be from
flavor_ref to flavor_ref_alt, another protection against attempting to
resize down.

This does add extra work, deleting a server after each test and making a
new one, however as it does away with resize direction ambiguity and
happy accidental successes the performance hit is worth it.

Change-Id: I7ba85c94d40927f31e1e07b9940e5a4ed1a7577f
Closes-Bug: #1450648

commit_message:
Support for verify option for examples and tests

Add support for the verify option for examples and tests.
Currently, OCC only supports the 'insecure' option as a boolean,
so we'll map that to the verify option.

Change-Id: I0761d01c74f8de5f9043332cecdc4b72ca730997

commit_message:
Fix publishing location of RST guides

Publish RST guides properly, we published them to e.g. user-guide/html/
instead of user-guide/. This is fixed with adding slashes to rsync so
that the first and the second parameter are equivalent.

Change-Id: Ie0842c19c45c5c99da3501303a453dd0920de74c

commit_message:
ml2: remove stale _filter_nets_l3 in get_networks

The commit of 0156ec175cc047826b211727d43d5d14a3e1f2d2
change-id of I47e01a11afaf6e6bcf06da7bd713fd39b05600ff
which fixes bug 1132849 removed the call of _filter_nets_l3 methods.
But somehow the fix missed ml2 plugin.
This patch fixes ml2 plugin and removes the unused mothod.

Change-Id: I4d13223c170fd6777773970e0d22a191b98dd5ee
Closes-Bug: #1382360

commit_message:
Remove HDS HUS iSCSI driver

Removes HDS HUS iSCSI driver as it's deprecated and will not be maintained anymore.

DocImpact

The documentation about HDS HUS iSCSI driver should be removed.

Change-Id: If30c3e183f8216a6a1406dfc8041a37b88132ac0

commit_message:
Remove nodes which failed to provision

Currently during provision some nodes may fail but provision
will success. This failed nodes are causing pre deployment actions
to fail.
This change removes failed nodes from deployment info and from all tasks.
It is safe to do because currently we allow only compute nodes to fail.

Change-Id: I5c3b677ca49ad9d2fd93a6ca1f524edc91e0766d
Closes-bug: #1438933

commit_message:
Replace ci.o.o links with docs.o.o/infra

The http://ci.openstack.org/ documentation site has been deprecated,
replaced by redirects to corresponding paths within
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/ where other Project Infrastructure
documentation already resides.

Change-Id: If4000b7f3366a028861698614bf67a3dfeb2ad10

[{'account_id': 16226, 'date': '2015-05-15 07:16:07.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2015-05-15 07:16:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

commit_message:
Bring Redhat support to acceptance tests

OpenStack Infra has jobs to run this on both Ubuntu Trusty and
OS7.

* Add minitest to Gemfile (dependency to run beaker on centos - see
  http://projects.theforeman.org/issues/2650 for details)
* separate nodepool files to have trusty & centos7 support in OS
* infra

Change-Id: I2cf4a54c324a289f99f3b4980a23b2d14f4cd2eb
Closes-bug: #1444736

commit_message:
Add SpawnFixture

This just turns spawn_n into a blocking passthrough so that we actually
run the spawned thing synchronously instead of not running it (and often
thinking we did).

Change-Id: I47ce83505361084e262843505031e3327d8e68a8

Fix class name of the base test case from oslotest

Delete cluster if another one is being deleted

  Make cluster's tasks locking by name.
  Add test TestTaskManagers.test_deletion_clusters_one_by_one()

commit_message:
Adding retry ability to neutronclient calls

All neutronclient calls wrapped in execute_with_retry
method to avoid occasional errors

partially implements bp clients-calls-retry

Change-Id: Ic6fe76d482533467ea50a6f35bd325270ada1db0

General comment:
Can we encapsulate all retries in appropriate methods in sahara/utils/openstack/ where OS clients reside. 

For example:

Now method assign_floating_ip in networks.py looks unreadable:

def assign_floating_ip(instance_id, pool):
    ip = b.execute_with_retries(nova.client().floating_ips.create, pool)
    server = b.execute_with_retries(nova.client().servers.get, instance_id)
    b.execute_with_retries(server.add_floating_ip, ip)

So I propose to add corresponding methods to nova.py like 

def create_floating_ip(pool):
    return b.execute_with_retries(nova.client().floating_ips.create, pool)'}, {'account_id': 6116, 'date': '2015-05-07 05:50:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Backup all data before upgrade and stop supervisor

Unfortunately, we have a puppet run inside containers on each start and
that's cause to the situation when old containers install new packages
on restart. We don't have this issue before because our containers won't
restarted during upgrade process and now they do (because of upgrading
Docker package).

As workaround, we have to:

* backup all data before starting upgrades
* stop supervisor before host system puppet run, so containers won't be
  restarted and hence won't install new packages

Still, it's hackish.. but I don't know better solution now :(

Closes-Bug: #1455419

Change-Id: I9522ab561718473873faa0f38c4cb34c3bee64b9
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

commit_message:
Log command failure details before raising ISCSITargetDetachFailed

In the case that there is some useful information in the
ProcessExecutionError (like stderr) when trying to terminate the
connection in the lio target, also log the error.

Related-Bug: #1450658

Change-Id: Id28968735eca27c4c4e5892e14d06aece02b06f5

commit_message:
Add support for preinstalled efi system partitions

Some distros have preinstalled efi system partitions.
On such systems, the image extension needn't run (rather
shouldn't run) grub-install command.  Instead, it should
just copy the contents to the efi system partition.

Closes-Bug: 1451635
Change-Id: I2af8a3b6a73b3d8be78c0d2877b32a1e986174ae

commit_message:
Adding ability to retry clients calls

* added execute_with_retries method
* added retries_number and retry_after config opts
* added unit tests that check that only specified errors
  will be retried

partially implements bp: clients-calls-retry

Change-Id: I59c27b1b9891900d9222fbe4303a33a31d749493

commit_message:
Fix MapR Oozie dependency resolution

Service dependencies should be overridden in every service version.
If not dependencies are installed w/o version i.e the latest ones

Change-Id: I7011425a00968e87e125172126c59b70f2160c8d
Closes-Bug: #1455483

commit_message:
Added dangling mock detection to 'dns' module

Ensured that no dangling mocks exist in the module by having each test
class extend trove_testtools.TestCase

Ran 'tox -epy27' and fixed any detected problems.

Change-Id: I5020c1d5dcb678957a21897daead7e794f7c408e
Partial-Bug: 1448273

commit_message:
Raise error once there's no deployment tasks in db

Added new exception 'NoDeploymentTasks' which is raised when user
is trying to manually deploy cluster whose release has empty
'deployment_tasks' and 'fuel_version' >= 6.1

Added loading of fake deployment tasks in both test Environment class
and 'loaddefault' command - so it also works in fake mode.

Change-Id: Ibaee6912cfbca27dbb35c4f9c09feb74c81b02a1
Closes-Bug: #1448066

[install-guide] Add WSGI keystone config for SUSE

Replace default eventlet front-end with Apache front-end to provide
a more production-style deployment.

Partially implements bp installguide-kilo.
