Looks good, but if we do that, I'm afraid that neutron-server with multiple workers won't work anymore. Neutron don't really use oslo.messaging in a good way. It fork the process after some TCP connections have been established.

Moving into the driver interface is a good idea, but because of neutron, you will have to handle what happen when the driver is forked. If a ZmqContext creates fd/pipe/socket, we need to close/reset/reopen them or creates a new ZmqContext object after the fork and don't reuse the parent process one. 

We already have qpid that doesn't work with neutron and multiple workers.

Some refs:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.messaging/transport.html#forking-processes-and-oslo-messaging-transport-objects
https://www.mail-archive.com/openstack-dev@lists.openstack.org/msg40648.html
https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/blob/master/oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_qpid.py#L600"}, {'account_id': 7805, 'date': '2015-03-18 10:09:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

In real deployments, neutron with multiple workers is very common and widely deployed in the production as far as I know.

This problem should be solved in advance.

ZmqContext-per-socket is not optimal at all but feasible to make it work.

If this optimal solution makes neutron broken, I don't think it is suitable to do it right now."}, {'account_id': 6804, 'date': '2015-03-18 19:23:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2015-03-19 10:40:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-03-21 13:23:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: -Verified

commit_message:
Create zmq context once per driver instance

Now the zmq context is created per each socket.
Such approach is not optimal. Create zmq context once per
driver instance and pass it as an argument to ZmqSocket contstructor.

Change-Id: I2dfa338bd9ea124e2b20a2150a42fb9bbcc25cee

commit_message:
LVM: Pass volume size in MiB to copy_volume() during volume migration

Currently migrate_volume() in lvm.py does not pass volume size in
MiB but passes volume size in GiB to copy_volume(). The size argument
of copy_volume() requires MiB value. As a result, if the volume size
is 1GiB, copy_volume() copies only 1MiB head of 1GiB volume to the
destination volume, and then the volume data is corrupted.
This patch fixes to pass volume size in MiB.

(cherry picked from commit a5da4c353a1df17341c1e745796e00a4ec1afd21)
Conflicts:
    cinder/tests/test_volume.py
    (Added mock for create_export. Changed to use contextlib.nested)

Change-Id: I8e06195dc3625ef07bc9858d844541e37a231b73
Closes-bug: #1454835

Hi tinytmy,

Your fix cleans up that problem.  But I have another minor observation (before your change): I see different behavior for 'Project' and 'Admin' panels.

Steps to reproduce:
1. login as admin
2. click 'System Panel' drop_arrow to hide panel.
3. Click on 'Identity Panel' to show panel.
4. Now click on Admin to hide
5. Click on Admin to show
==> Identity is open (as expected).

However...
6. Now click on Project (Compute panel is open)
7. Click on 'Compute' to hide
8. Click on 'Orchestration' to show
9. Click on Project to hide
10. Click on Project to show
==> Compute is always open by default.  Do we want this behavior?"}, {'account_id': 9961, 'date': '2014-05-22 00:58:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Ok so I think this is basically there.

Remaining thoughts:
 - use testscenarios and put the input config text and the expected extras_require subdict as the parameters to each scenario.
 - I think this is small enough we can do the requirements.txt processing of the same stuff at the same time.

For that you need to:
 - split the install_requires requirements on ; into requirement, marker
 - turn install_requires things with markers into the extra ':marker'.

I suspect that the easiest way to do this is to rearrange things a little:
in the requirements process above capture the markers so you have a list of tuples(req, marker-or-''). put that in a dict as {'':thelist}
first pass on extras, insert into that same dict {extra:list-of-(req,marker-or-'')}

The process that dict into the final extras (which will naturally create extras with ':marker' as we need from install_requires.

Finally say install_requires = extras.pop('', [])
and you'll have a nicely processed install_requires, and a nicely processed extras dict, in a single code flow."}, {'account_id': 9453, 'date': '2015-05-13 00:56:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

commit_message:
Teach pbr to read extras and env markers

This adds support for reading extras from setup.cfg.

It also adds support for handling environment markers, both in the
extras section and in install_requires and in requirements.txt.

Change-Id: I6fd8276012e65f82934df9c374613b1ce6856b5a

commit_message:
Remove RST tags user_only and admin_only

These tags are now completely unused, remove them from scripts setting
them.

Now we can simplify publishdocs.sh with a simple loop instead of
separate invocations.

Remove our scope sphinx extensions, it's not needed anymore.
Remove also the hot extension from the Admin User Guide, it's only used
in the End User Guide.

Change-Id: Ib6c9f35e336ee13b84030a6e7164dea27d621e67

commit_message:
Fix the ipaddress validate issue

Right now the jenkins jobs all failed with ipv4address validate.
We make ipaddress check logic use netaddr

If wsme have better IPv4AddressType changes or magnum api types usage
was not right, we can change latter. Right now, we should
make magnum work.

For netaddr it has been include in global-requirements

For wsme IPv4AddressType, check
ttps://github.com/stackforge/wsme/blob/master/wsme/types.py

Closes-Bug: #1455405
Co-Authored-By: Davanum Srinivas <davanum@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I67e6c9e0377103bf5b0cd4d120c146ef2366f440

commit_message:
Fixed issue with join function args

During the refactoring of OSTF code we added
new bug to OSTF tests, join function takes only one arg
and we have to use format function instead of join here.

Change-Id: Ie104988d6e64c22aa48e89ab1efecf797b29a427
Closes-Bug: #1452592

commit_message:
Allow using relative path from user home for SSHClient.upload()

os.path.isdir("~/any/path") return False for paths with '~', so
the path should be prepared.

Closes-Bug:#1447470
Change-Id: Ib339f494f39b14606ae516619341a4f3d980f4b4

commit_message:
Replace ci.o.o links with docs.o.o/infra

The http://ci.openstack.org/ documentation site has been deprecated,
replaced by redirects to corresponding paths within
http://docs.openstack.org/infra/ where other Project Infrastructure
documentation already resides.

Change-Id: I5b7d2d6699084cce38a4d1a84ebfc42f8a53624e

commit_message:
Remove unused wrapper methods

There are some wrapper methods in base.py of messaging tests but
get_single_message and get_multiple_messages are not used at all.
These methods just call client methods without any special behaviors
and they seems redundant. So this patch removes them.

Change-Id: I596a1089c4bfb66b7daf1b27779208920d251e63

commit_message:
Disable test check disk space for 6.1

Test chaeck if there is warning message  in sheduler log,
and in case if it is - test fails,
but at the same time cluster works fine,
hypervisor details show all neccessary space.
So we need to correct test case here .
For 6.1 we just disable this tests, for 7.0 we need to correct the scenario

Change-Id: Id18ce8cc60e3c121072f7753274e9bdca714f015
Releated-Bug: #1452569

commit_message:
Fix the ipaddress validate issue

Jenkins jobs fail currently since something triggered
the use of ipaddress instead of ipaddr in wsme.

A lot of openstack projects use netaddr for validation, so
we have to create a custom wsme type using netaddr to
be independent of the vagaries of ipaddr/ipaddress with
wsme's built in type.

Closes-Bug: #1455405
Co-Authored-By: Davanum Srinivas <davanum@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I42ba7e58d1d7c3a3032308329ab1d4665332d195

commit_message:
Fix pip-missing-reqs

The gate-nova-pip-missing-reqs job on the experimental queue is failing
and pointing out several missing runtime dependencies from
requirements.txt.

Also, we need to ignore the nova/test.py file during the scan since
pip-missing-reqs doesn't include test-requirements.txt.

requests
--------
nova/scheduler/filters/trusted_filter.py:50 dist=requests
nova/api/ec2/__init__.py:30 dist=requests

prettytable
-----------
nova/openstack/common/cliutils.py:29 dist=prettytable

python-keystoneclient
---------------------
nova/context.py:22 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/network/neutronv2/api.py:21 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/compute/manager.py:42 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/volume/cinder.py:27 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/context.py:23 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/network/neutronv2/api.py:23 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/network/neutronv2/api.py:24 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/volume/cinder.py:28 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/keymgr/barbican.py:25 dist=python-keystoneclient
nova/network/neutronv2/api.py:22 dist=python-keystoneclient

netifaces
---------
nova/compute/utils.py:21 dist=netifaces

setuptools
----------
nova/openstack/common/versionutils.py:26 dist=setuptools
nova/virt/xenapi/image/bittorrent.py:18 dist=setuptools

Closes-Bug: #1453857

Change-Id: If880d76cf3e47c14b370d63313330996e09f5ab8

commit_message:
Introduce `valid_command' validator

Introduce `valid_command' validator that checks whether the specified
command dictionary is a valid one.

Change-Id: I1645c25f5a0332ee7cf5b76bc987a8e4d6913f7a
Implements: blueprint vm-workloads-framework

commit_message:
Rsync: rewrite to use raw commands, not fabric

This is because we will be using SSH hops to rsync into slave nodes.
Fabric doesn't seem to support this out of the box.

Change-Id: Idf43d7b6c35324ade9be3467cee7c664833a38a8

commit_message:
Could not find resource Service[undef] for relationship from Package.

Original variables were not assign any value. Therefore puppet will try
to find Service[undef].

Adjust those service's title to correctly parameter location at
ceilometer's class.

Change-Id: Ibe7c0ea1c12d2bcd7e1a062a237dccd8a3d36ef8
Closes-Bug: #1455029

commit_message:
heat_keystone README update for service and endpoint

Updates the heat_keystone README with following entries:
- OS::Keystone::Service
- OS::Keystone::Endpoint
- keystone.service custom constrain

implements blueprint keystone-resource-service-endpoint

Change-Id: I4e844bc2d31791cd03159cf5b6252f9ebd422a1d

Resource plug-in for keystone service

Adds contrib resource plug-in for keystone service.

implments blueprint keystone-resource-service-endpoint

Change-Id: I002cc9d6a5c2156c015535c163f8a61a8441737e
